---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'Cursor AI Code Editor Review: AI-Powered Development Environment',
  description: 'Cursor is an AI code editor built on VS Code. Integrated AI assistant. $20/month for Pro. Free tier available. Best for developers who want AI pair programming while coding.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['Cursor review', 'Cursor AI', 'AI code editor', 'Cursor vs VS Code', 'Cursor pricing'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-[#000000]/5 to-[#333333]/5 py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-gray-900 mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        AI Tool Review · 2025 Updated
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        Cursor AI Code Editor Review
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        Cursor is VS Code with AI superpowers. It's an AI code editor with integrated AI assistant. Write code faster. Debug easier. Learn while coding. $20/month for Pro. Free tier with limited AI. Best for developers who want AI pair programming, not website building.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold mb-2">
          Quick verdict: Cursor is excellent if you're a developer who codes. Not a website builder like Framer or Durable. Think of it as VS Code with an AI pair programmer built in. Great for speeding up development, learning new codebases, and debugging. Not for non-developers.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Cursor Is -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Cursor Actually Is
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold mb-3">Cursor is:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>AI code editor:</strong> Built on VS Code</li>
          <li>• <strong>AI integrated:</strong> AI assistant built into editor</li>
          <li>• <strong>Code-aware:</strong> Understands your codebase context</li>
          <li>• <strong>Chat interface:</strong> Ask questions about your code</li>
          <li>• <strong>Autocomplete:</strong> AI suggests code as you type</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">What makes Cursor different:</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Cursor is VS Code with AI deeply integrated:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Familiar interface:</strong> If you know VS Code, you know Cursor</li>
          <li>• <strong>Full codebase awareness:</strong> AI understands entire project</li>
          <li>• <strong>Multi-file editing:</strong> AI can change files across your project</li>
          <li>• <strong>Terminal integration:</strong> AI can run commands for you</li>
          <li>• <strong>Local first:</strong> Your code stays on your machine</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Not like ChatGPT:</strong> Cursor knows your code. ChatGPT doesn't (unless you paste everything).</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold mb-3">What Cursor is NOT:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Not a website builder (no drag-and-drop)</li>
          <li>• Not for non-developers (need to know code)</li>
          <li>• Not a replacement for understanding code</li>
          <li>• Not magic (AI makes mistakes, you must review)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How Cursor Works -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      How Cursor Works
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold mb-3">1. Codebase Indexing</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">When you open a project, Cursor indexes your entire codebase. It understands file relationships, imports, dependencies. AI knows context across all files.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold mb-3">2. AI Chat</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Ask questions in chat: "How does authentication work?" "Fix this bug" "Add error handling." AI reads your code and answers with code suggestions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold mb-3">3. Code Autocomplete</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">As you type, AI suggests completions. Press Tab to accept. Like GitHub Copilot but aware of your entire codebase.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold mb-3">4. Multi-file Edits</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">AI can suggest changes across multiple files at once. "Add logging to all API endpoints" - AI creates changes across all relevant files.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Cursor is Good At -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Cursor is Good At
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">1. Understanding Codebases</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Cursor excels at explaining code:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>"How does this work?"</strong> AI explains any function</li>
          <li>• <strong>"Where is this used?"</strong> AI finds references across codebase</li>
          <li>• <strong>"What does this file do?"</strong> AI summarizes purpose</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Use case:</strong> Joining a new project. Understanding unfamiliar code. Learning new frameworks.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">2. Writing Boilerplate</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Cursor generates repetitive code fast:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Component templates</li>
          <li>• API endpoint scaffolding</li>
          <li>• Test file structure</li>
          <li>• Configuration files</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Benefit:</strong> Skip boring setup work. Focus on unique logic.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">3. Debugging Help</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Cursor helps find bugs:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• "Why is this crashing?"</li>
          <li>• "Find the bug in this function"</li>
          <li>• "Explain this error message"</li>
          <li>• "How do I fix this?"</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Benefit:</strong> Faster debugging. AI spots patterns you miss.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">4. Refactoring</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Cursor suggests code improvements:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• "Make this more readable"</li>
          <li>• "Extract this into a function"</li>
          <li>• "Add error handling"</li>
          <li>• "Optimize this query"</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Benefit:</strong> Cleaner code. Less technical debt.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">5. Learning While Coding</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Great educational tool:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Ask "why" about code patterns</li>
          <li>• Get explanations for unfamiliar syntax</li>
          <li>• See alternative implementations</li>
          <li>• Learn best practices in real-time</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Benefit:</strong> Learn from AI suggestions. Improve your coding skills.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Cursor is Bad At -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Cursor is Bad At
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">1. Non-Developers</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Cursor requires coding knowledge:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Must know programming language syntax</li>
          <li>• Must understand code structure</li>
          <li>• Must debug AI suggestions (AI makes mistakes)</li>
          <li>• Must test that code actually works</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Not for you if:</strong> You don't know how to code. Cursor doesn't replace developer skills.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">2. Large-Scale Architecture</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">AI struggles with big picture:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• System design is hit-or-miss</li>
          <li>• Performance optimization suggestions vary</li>
          <li>• Security considerations need human review</li>
          <li>• Scalability advice is generic</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Use for:</strong> Implementation details, not architectural decisions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">3. Hallucinations</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">AI makes things up sometimes:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Invents functions that don't exist</li>
          <li>• Suggests imports from wrong packages</li>
          <li>• Confidently writes broken code</li>
          <li>• Doesn't always know latest API changes</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Rule:</strong> Never trust AI blindly. Always test. Always review code.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">4. Context Limits</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Large codebases exceed AI memory:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• AI might miss files in huge projects</li>
          <li>• Context window limits apply</li>
          <li>• Performance slows on big codebases</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Workaround:</strong> Keep AI focused on specific files or modules.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Cursor Pricing
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">FREE (Limited)</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Cost:</strong> $0</li>
          <li>• <strong>AI requests:</strong> Limited (200 fast requests per month)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Features:</strong> Basic AI chat, autocomplete</li>
          <li>• <strong>Best for:</strong> Trying Cursor, occasional use</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold mb-3">Pro: $20/month</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>AI requests:</strong> Unlimited fast requests</li>
          <li>• <strong>Features:</strong> Everything in Free + advanced features</li>
          <li>• <strong>Best for:</strong> Daily coding, serious development</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold mb-3">Business: $40/user/month</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Everything in Pro</strong></li>
          <li>• <strong>Centralized billing</strong></li>
          <li>• <strong>Admin controls</strong></li>
          <li>• <strong>Best for:</strong> Teams and companies</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Cursor vs Alternatives -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Cursor vs Alternatives
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold"></th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Cursor</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">GitHub Copilot</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">ChatGPT</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Type</td>
            <td class="p-4">AI code editor</td>
            <td class="p-4">VS Code extension</td>
            <td class="p-4">Chat interface</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Codebase awareness</td>
            <td class="p-4">Full project</td>
            <td class="p-4">Current file</td>
            <td class="p-4">None (unless pasted)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Interface</td>
            <td class="p-4">Built-in editor</td>
            <td class="p-4">Extension</td>
            <td class="p-4">Separate chat</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Multi-file edits</td>
            <td class="p-4">Yes</td>
            <td class="p-4">No</td>
            <td class="p-4">No</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Pricing</td>
            <td class="p-4">$20/mo Pro</td>
            <td class="p-4">$10/mo</td>
            <td class="p-4">$20/mo Plus</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Best for</td>
            <td class="p-4">Deep codebase work</td>
            <td class="p-4">Autocomplete</td>
            <td class="p-4">Questions, research</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom Line -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-6">Bottom Line</h2>

      <p class="text-lg mb-6">Cursor is VS Code with AI superpowers. If you're a developer, it's like having a pair programmer who knows your entire codebase. Not magic, but significantly faster than coding without AI.</p>

      <p class="text-lg mb-6"><strong>Use Cursor if:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• You're a developer who codes daily</li>
        <li>• You work in large codebases</li>
        <li>• You want AI integrated into your editor</li>
        <li>• You're willing to pay $20/month for productivity</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg mb-6"><strong>Use GitHub Copilot if:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• You want cheaper AI autocomplete ($10/mo)</li>
        <li>• You're happy with VS Code + extension</li>
        <li>• You don't need multi-file AI edits</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg mb-6"><strong>Use ChatGPT if:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• You want research and explanations</li>
        <li>• You don't need editor integration</li>
        <li>• You're okay with copy-pasting code snippets</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg"><strong>Don't use Cursor if:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3">
        <li>• You don't know how to code (not a beginner tool)</li>
        <li>• You want a website builder (use Framer or Durable)</li>
        <li>• You rarely code (not worth the subscription)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related AI Tool Reviews
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/v0-review" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">v0.dev Review</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">AI code generator by Vercel</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/durable-review" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Durable AI Review</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">AI website builder for service businesses</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
